  "prompt": "My age is 14. Can I go to the gym?",
  "response": "Yes, at 14 years old, you can typically go to the gym, but there are a few things to consider. Many gyms have age restrictions and may require a parent or guardian's permission for minors. It's also important to ensure that you're using equipment safely and following a suitable workout plan. Some gyms offer youth programs or can provide guidance on appropriate exercise for your age. It\u2019s always a good idea to consult with a coach or trainer for advice on starting a fitness routine.",
